
[1]recluse

   RECLU'SE, a.

   Shut up; sequestered; retired from the world or from public notice;
   solitary; as a recluse monk or hermit; a recluse life.

   I all the live-long day consume in meditation deep, recluse from human
   converse.

                                RECLU'SE, n.

   1. A person who live in retirement or seclusion from intercourse with
   the world; as a hermit or monk.

   2. A person who confines himself to a cell in a monastery.
